INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES (1,1,'user','Hello, my name is Mor','2026-06-16 10:37:18'),(2,1,'assistant','Hello, Mor! How can I assist you today?','2026-06-16 10:37:21'),(3,1,'user','can you tell me my name?','2026-06-16 10:37:49'),(4,1,'assistant','Yes, your name is Mor! How can I help you today, Mor?','2026-06-16 10:37:50'),(5,2,'user','היי, קוראים לי מור','2026-06-16 10:39:59'),(6,2,'assistant','היי מור! איך אני יכול לעזור לך היום?','2026-06-16 10:40:00'),(7,2,'user','תוכל להגיד לי איך קוראים לי?','2026-06-16 10:40:11'),(8,2,'assistant','כן, כמובן! קוראים לך מור. איך אפשר לעזור לך היום, מור?','2026-06-16 10:40:12'),(9,2,'user','תוכל לספר לי על סוגי פרחים?\nאני מאוד אוהבת פרחים לבנים,\nאשמח לדעת על סוגי פרחים, מה המקור שלהם, טווחי מחירים, האם הם מסמלים משהו, מתי מקובל לתת אותם\nאולי על שילובים פרחים מומלצים ועוד','2026-06-16 10:42:28'),(10,2,'assistant','בהחלט! פרחים הם רעיון נפלא ומרהיב. המידע הבא יתמקד בסוגי פרחים לבנים, אך גם ייתן מבוא לגבי פרחים באופן כללי.\n\n### סוגי פרחים לבנים:\n\n1. **ורד לבן**:\n   - **מקור**: רובם מגיעים מאירופה ואסיה.\n   - **סמליות**: אהבה טהורה, תמימות וזוגיות.\n   - **טווח מחירים**: בין 15-30 ₪ לורד.\n   - **מתי מקובל לתת**: כשיש חתונה, טקסים דתיים או לאירועים רומנטיים.\n\n2. **ליליה**:\n   - **מקור**: נחשבת מקורית לאירואסיה. \n   - **סמליות**: טוהר וחסד.\n   - **טווח מחירים**: בין 20-50 ₪ לפרח.\n   - **מתי מקובל לתת**: באירועים כמו לידות או חגים.\n\n3. **גיבסנית** (Baby\'s Breath):\n   - **מקור**: באירופה ובצפון אמריקה.\n   - **סמליות**: תמימות ורכות.\n   - **טווח מחירים**: בין 10-25 ₪ לזריחה.\n   - **מתי מקובל לתת**: בעיקר בשילוב עם פרחים אחרים בזרי כלה.\n\n4. **ציפורן (Carnation)**:\n   - **מקור**: נחשבת לאחד הפרחים העתיקים ביותר.\n   - **סמליות**: אהבה עזה, השראה ונאמנות.\n   - **טווח מחירים**: בין 5-15 ₪ לצמח.\n   - **מתי מקובל לתת**: באירועים שונים כמו ימי הולדת וחגיגות.\n\n5. **מרגריטה**:\n   - **מקור**: מהנחלים ברחבי אירופה ובאמריקה.\n   - **סמליות**: אהבה נאמנה ומתוקה.\n   - **טווח מחירים**: בין 10-20 ₪ לכל פרח.\n   - **מתי מקובל לתת**: מתנה לאירועים כמו ימי הולדת או הוקרה.\n\n### שילובים מומלצים:\n- **ורדים לבנים וקלות**: שילוב ייחודי שמקנה זר לבן קלאסי.\n- **ליליות ופרחי גיבסנית**: נותן מראה עדין ורומנטי.\n- **מרגריטות עם קונקולריות**: שילוב להוסיף צבע, ויוצר תחושת רעננות.\n\n### טיפ כללי:\n- אם את בוחרת לקטוף פרחים מהגן או מהשדה, הקפידי על חוקי הקטיף המקומיים.\n- תמיד יש לשקול את עונת השנה והאם הפרחים זמינים.\n\nאם יש שאלות נוספות או אם יש משהו אחר שתרצי לדעת על פרחים, אני כאן!','2026-06-16 10:42:40'),(11,3,'user','Hi, my name is Mor, and I want to talk about Marvel. What can you tell me about this cinematic universe?','2026-06-16 10:45:32'),(12,3,'assistant','Hi Mor! I\'d be happy to talk about the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU). The MCU is a franchise and shared universe centered around a series of superhero films and television series produced by Marvel Studios, based on characters that appear in American comic books published by Marvel Comics.\n\n**Key Elements of the MCU:**\n\n1. **Phases**: The MCU is organized into phases that consist of multiple films and shows. \n   - **Phase One** (2008-2012): Introduced key characters, culminating in \"The Avengers.\"\n   - **Phase Two** (2013-2015): Expanded the universe with sequels and new characters, ending with \"Ant-Man.\"\n   - **Phase Three** (2016-2019): Focused on deeper storytelling and character development, concluding with \"Spider-Man: Far From Home.\"\n   - **Phase Four** (2021-2022): Introduced new stories and characters through Disney+ series like \"WandaVision,\" \"Loki,\" and films like \"Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings.\"\n   - **Phases Five and Six** are currently unfolding, exploring new narratives and characters, including major events like \"Avengers: The Kang Dynasty\" and \"Avengers: Secret Wars.\"\n\n2. **Characters**: The MCU features a wide variety of characters, including iconic superheroes such as Iron Man, Captain America, Thor, Black Widow, Hulk, Doctor Strange, Spider-Man, and newer characters like Ms. Marvel and Shang-Chi. \n\n3. **Storytelling**: One of the franchise\'s defining features is its interconnected storytelling, where events in one film or series often impact others. This creates a web of narratives that audiences have come to love.\n\n4. **Diversity of Media**: In addition to films, the MCU includes television shows on various platforms, animated series, and even comic books that explore side stories and character arcs further.\n\n5. **Themes**: The MCU often explores themes such as heroism, responsibility, sacrifice, identity, and the consequences of power. These themes resonate with audiences and contribute to character depth and development.\n\n6. **Cultural Impact**: The MCU has had a significant impact on popular culture, setting box office records and influencing filmmaking trends towards interconnected universes.\n\nIf you\'re interested in specific movies, characters, themes, or events within the MCU, feel free to ask!','2026-06-16 10:45:38'),(13,3,'user','Phase One is my favorite.','2026-06-16 10:46:41'),(14,3,'assistant','Phase One of the Marvel Cinematic Universe is indeed a beloved part of the franchise and laid the groundwork for what would become a massive cinematic universe. Here’s a brief rundown of the key films in Phase One along with some highlights:\n\n1. **Iron Man (2008)**: Directed by Jon Favreau, this film introduced Tony Stark, played by Robert Downey Jr. The story follows Stark as he invents the Iron Man suit and ultimately becomes a hero. This film established the tone for the MCU, mixing humor, action, and character development.\n\n2. **The Incredible Hulk (2008)**: Directed by Louis Leterrier, this film stars Edward Norton as Bruce Banner. It explores Hulk\'s origins and his struggle to control his alter ego while being pursued by General Ross. Although it didn\'t connect as strongly as others, it set up the foundation for Hulk\'s character.\n\n3. **Iron Man 2 (2010)**: This sequel expands on Tony Stark\'s story, dealing with his legacy and introducing new characters like Black Widow (Scarlett Johansson) and War Machine (Don Cheadle). It also begins to tease the larger universe with references to S.H.I.E.L.D. and the Avengers Initiative.\n\n4. **Thor (2011)**: Directed by Kenneth Branagh, this film introduces Thor (Chris Hemsworth), the God of Thunder, and explores his banishment to Earth. We also meet Loki (Tom Hiddleston), adding complexity to the story with themes of family, betrayal, and redemption.\n\n5. **Captain America: The First Avenger (2011)**: Set during World War II, this film tells the origin story of Steve Rogers (Chris Evans) as he transforms from a frail man into Captain America. It’s notable for its themes of patriotism and sacrifice and for introducing the Tesseract, an important artifact in the MCU.\n\n6. **The Avengers (2012)**: Directed by Joss Whedon, this film is the culmination of Phase One, bringing together all the major heroes to form the Avengers team in response to Loki\'s invasion of Earth. It was a milestone in cinematic history, showcasing the successful integration of multiple storylines and characters.\n\n**Highlights of Phase One**:\n- **Character Development**: Each film had a strong focus on character backstories and motivations, allowing audiences to connect deeply with the heroes.\n- **Humor and Wit**: The blend of humor with action and drama became a hallmark of the MCU.\n- **The Avengers Initiative**: The idea of a connected universe was introduced gradually, keeping audiences excited for the eventual team-up.\n\nPhase One not only achieved critical and commercial success but also set a benchmark for how superhero films could be made and interconnected. What are some of your favorite moments or characters from this phase?','2026-06-16 10:46:49'),(15,3,'user','My favorite character is Loki','2026-06-16 10:47:13'),(16,3,'assistant','Loki is a fascinating and multi-dimensional character within the Marvel Cinematic Universe! Portrayed by Tom Hiddleston, Loki Odinson has captivated audiences with his complex personality, charm, and cunning nature. Here are some key aspects of Loki’s character in the MCU:\n\n### 1. **Origins**:\n- Loki is introduced as the adopted brother of Thor and the God of Mischief. His complicated relationship with Thor adds depth to his character, as he often struggles with feelings of inadequacy and jealousy, particularly regarding his status as the heir to the throne of Asgard.\n\n### 2. **The Dark World**:\n- In “Thor” (2011), we see Loki’s jealousy towards Thor and his desire for approval from his father, Odin. This sets the stage for his later actions and motivations. In “The Avengers” (2012), he becomes the primary antagonist, wielding the power of the Tesseract to subjugate Earth, showcasing his ambitious and manipulative side.\n\n### 3. **Complexity and Redemption**:\n- Loki\'s character evolves throughout the MCU. In “Thor: The Dark World,” and later in “Thor: Ragnarok” (2017), we see glimpses of his redemption as he helps Thor battle Hela. This complexity makes him one of the more relatable villains within the MCU, as he constantly navigates between his desire for power and his ties to his family.\n\n### 4. **The Loki Series**:\n- The series “Loki,” released on Disney+ in 2021, explores the character further, focusing on a variant of Loki who escapes with the Tesseract during the events of “Avengers: Endgame.” This series dives deep into themes of identity, free will, and time, introducing new characters like Mobius M. Mobius (Owen Wilson) and exploring the multiverse through the Time Variance Authority (TVA).\n\n### 5. **Themes**:\n- Loki embodies themes of identity, belonging, and the struggle between good and evil. His journey grapples with self-acceptance and the consequences of his past actions, leaving audiences wondering whether he can truly change.\n\n### 6. **Humor and Charm**:\n- Loki’s wit and humor are integral to his character. Tom Hiddleston delivers his lines with charisma and charm, making even his more mischievous acts oddly endearing. His snarky remarks and playful banter lighten tense moments, making him a favorite among fans.\n\nLoki\'s journey from villain to anti-hero to someone seeking redemption is one of the most compelling character arcs in the MCU. Do you have a favorite scene or quote involving Loki that stands out to you?','2026-06-16 10:47:22'),(17,3,'user','\"i have been falling for 30 minutes\"','2026-06-16 10:48:07'),(18,3,'assistant','That quote, “I’ve been falling for 30 minutes!” is one of Loki\'s most memorable and humorous lines from \"Thor: Ragnarok\" (2017). It occurs during a scene where Loki is literally falling through the air after he is thrown out of the Bifrost by Thor. This moment captures Loki\'s blend of vulnerability and charm, as he turns a potentially dire situation into a humorous observation.\n\nLoki\'s ability to maintain humor even in moments of peril adds to the audience\'s affection for him. This line not only highlights his comedic timing but also emphasizes the film\'s overall lighter tone compared to the previous Thor installments. \"Thor: Ragnarok,\" directed by Taika Waititi, revitalized Loki’s character, showcasing his more playful and entertaining side while still acknowledging his more serious and complex background.\n\nAre there other moments or themes around Loki that you particularly enjoy?','2026-06-16 10:48:10'),(19,3,'user','My favorite movie is Thor: Ragnarok.','2026-06-16 10:51:43'),(20,3,'assistant','\"Thor: Ragnarok\" is a standout film in the MCU and a fan favorite for many reasons! Directed by Taika Waititi, it successfully blends action, humor, and character development, resulting in a fresh take on Thor and the Asgardian mythos. Here are some highlights and reasons why it resonates with fans:\n\n### 1. **Tone and Humor**:\n- One of the most significant shifts in \"Thor: Ragnarok\" is its comedic tone. Taika Waititi introduced a more light-hearted and irreverent style, embracing humor throughout the film. The witty dialogue, visual gags, and playful character interactions create a fun atmosphere that sets it apart from previous Thor films.\n\n### 2. **Character Development**:\n- Thor (Chris Hemsworth) undergoes significant growth in this film. He learns to rely on his friends and lets go of the idea of being a singular hero. The dynamic between him and Hulk (Mark Ruffalo) is especially enjoyable, full of banter and camaraderie.\n- Loki (Tom Hiddleston) also has a pivotal role, showcasing his evolving relationship with Thor. Their brotherly bond is tested but ultimately strengthened as they face new challenges together.\n\n### 3. **Introduction of New Characters**:\n- The film introduces exciting new characters like Valkyrie (Tessa Thompson), who brings strength and complexity to the narrative, and Hela (Cate Blanchett), the powerful and compelling villainess. Hela’s motivations and presence add a formidable challenge for Thor and Loki.\n\n### 4. **Visual Style**:\n- \"Thor: Ragnarok\" is visually stunning, with vibrant colors, imaginative set designs, and epic action sequences. The aesthetics pay homage to classic comic book art, contributing to the film\'s unique feel.\n\n### 5. **Themes**:\n- The film explores themes of identity, family, loss, and the idea of renewal. Thor learns to embrace his true power beyond just his hammer and recognizes the importance of his allies and what it means to be a leader.\n\n### 6. **Memorable Scenes and Quotes**:\n- From the hilarious introduction of the Grandmaster (Jeff Goldblum) to the iconic \"Get help!\" scene, the film is packed with memorable moments that resonate with fans. The climax with the Battle of Asgard and Thor’s ultimate acceptance of his role as a hero leaves a lasting impact.\n\n### 7. **Post-Credits Scenes**:\n- Like many MCU films, \"Thor: Ragnarok\" features post-credits scenes that tease future plots and connect to the broader universe, particularly hinting at the events leading to \"Avengers: Infinity War.\"\n\nOverall, \"Thor: Ragnarok\" manages to balance its comedic elements with genuine emotional moments, making it a well-rounded and enjoyable film. It successfully reinvigorated the Thor franchise and has left a lasting legacy in the MCU. What are some of your favorite scenes or elements from the movie?','2026-06-16 10:51:52'),(21,4,'user','היי, תספר לי בדיחה על ציפורים','2026-06-16 11:19:26'),(22,4,'assistant','בוודאי! למה הציפור לא עשתה את העבודה שלה?\n\nכי היא תמיד הייתה \"עפה\" מהעניין! ??','2026-06-16 11:19:28'),(23,4,'user','מצחיק, יש לך בדיחה טובה יותר?','2026-06-16 11:19:47'),(24,4,'assistant','כמובן! מה עושות שתי ציפורים על עץ?\n\nחכות שהדואר יגיע! ???','2026-06-16 11:19:48'),(25,4,'user','לא הבנתי את הבדיחה, תוכל לספר אחת נוספת?','2026-06-16 11:20:13'),(26,4,'assistant','בטח! מה אומרת התוכי כשהיא נכנסת לחנות?\n\n\"אני רוצה לקנות משהו... אבל לא עף-בה!\" ??','2026-06-16 11:20:14'),(27,4,'user','איזה ציפור הכי נדירה בעולם?','2026-06-16 11:20:53'),(28,4,'assistant','אחת הציפורים הנדירות בעולם היא הציפור בשם **קאקפו** (Kākāpō), שהיא תוכי עף בלתי-יכולה מאוד מאיים על הכחדה ומצויה בניו זילנד. יש לה מספר מאוד נמוך של פרטים וקיימת תוכנית שימור פעילה להצלתה. ישנן גם ציפורים נדירות נוספות, כמו ה**ברבור השחור** ואפילו ה**ציפור הכחולה המזרחית**, אבל הקאקפו נחשבת לאחת הנדירות ביותר.','2026-06-16 11:20:55'),(29,5,'user','שלום, קוראים לי מור','2026-06-16 11:23:28'),(30,5,'assistant','שלום מור! איך אני יכול לעזור לך היום?','2026-06-16 11:23:29'),(31,5,'user','איך קוראים לי?','2026-06-16 11:23:36'),(32,5,'assistant','קוראים לך מור. איך אפשר לעזור לך היום?','2026-06-16 11:23:37'),(33,5,'user','איזה שפת תכנות, הכי נפוצה בעולם, בחלק השרת?','2026-06-16 11:24:42'),(34,5,'assistant','נכון ל-2023, שפת התכנות הנפוצה ביותר בחלק השרת היא לרוב **JavaScript**, ובפרט גירסתה Node.js שמשמשת לפיתוח צד השרת. שפות נוספות שהן מאוד פופולריות בחלק השרת כוללות את **Python**, **Java**, **PHP** ו-**C#**. \n\nהבחירה בשפה תלויה בגורמים כמו סוג הפרויקט, דרישות הביצועים, והעדפות הצוות. אם יש לך שאלות נוספות על שפות תכנות או טכנולוגיות אחרות, אני כאן לעזור!','2026-06-16 11:24:45'),(35,5,'user','ובצד הלקוח?','2026-06-16 11:25:18'),(36,5,'assistant','בצד הלקוח, שפת התכנות הנפוצה ביותר היא **JavaScript**. זהו הסטנדרט לפיתוח אינטרנטי בצד הלקוח, ומגוון ספריות כמו **React**, **Vue.js** ו-**Angular** מתבססות עליה.\n\nבנוסף, HTML ו-CSS הם קריטיים לפיתוח בצד הלקוח, כיוון שהם מספקים את המבנה (HTML) והעיצוב (CSS) של הדפים. \n\nאם יש לך שאלות נוספות לגבי פיתוח צד הלקוח או טכנולוגיות אחרות, אני כאן לעזור!','2026-06-16 11:25:21');
